Package au.csiro.pathling.fhir

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    TerminologyClient
    A HAPI "annotation client" for communicating with a R4 FHIR terminology service.
    TerminologyServiceFactory
    Represents something that creates a TerminologyService.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ConformanceProvider
    This class provides a customised CapabilityStatement describing the functionality of the analytics server.
    DefaultTerminologyServiceFactory
    Default implementation of TerminologyServiceFactory providing TerminologyService implemented using TerminologyClient with given configuration.
    Dependencies
    Provides beans used within processing of FHIR requests within the server.
    ErrorHandlingInterceptor
    This class unifies exception handling.
    ErrorReportingInterceptor
    This class intercepts errors and reports them to Sentry.
    FhirContextFactory
    Uses the FhirEncoders class to create a FhirContext.
    FhirServer
    A HAPI RestfulServer that provides the FHIR interface to the functionality within Pathling.
    OperationDefinitionProvider
    This class is used for serving up the OperationDefinition resources which describe this server's FHIR API.
    RequestIdInterceptor
    This class adds the HAPI request ID to the logging context.
    ResourceProviderFactory
    A factory that encapsulates creation of resource specific ResourceProviders.
    SmartConfigurationInterceptor
    This class intercepts requests to `.well-known/smart-configuration` and returns a Well-Known Uniform Resource Identifiers document with the configured authorization URIs.
